# Fix $HOME Not Expanding in Docker Volume Path

## Root cause

`h.RunnerDir(instanceName)` returns the shell variable string `"$HOME/.gh-sr/runners/<name>"`. When this is wrapped in `posixSingleQuote()`, single quotes prevent shell expansion, so Docker receives the literal `$HOME` rather than `/home/an-lee`.

## Fix in [internal/runner/container.go](internal/runner/container.go)

Add a `resolveAbsoluteRunnerDir` helper that runs `echo $HOME` once on the host and substitutes the result into the path:

```go
// resolveAbsoluteRunnerDir returns the absolute path for the runner state
// directory on the host, expanding $HOME to its real value.
// h.RunnerDir returns a shell-variable string ("$HOME/...") which must not
// appear inside single quotes in Docker arguments.
func resolveAbsoluteRunnerDir(h *host.Host, instanceName string) (string, error) {
    dir := h.RunnerDir(instanceName)
    if !strings.HasPrefix(dir, "$HOME") {
        return dir, nil
    }
    out, err := h.Run("echo $HOME")
    if err != nil {
        return "", fmt.Errorf("resolving home dir: %w", err)
    }
    home := strings.TrimSpace(out)
    return home + dir[len("$HOME"):], nil
}
```

Then in `setupContainer`, replace:
```go
stateDir := containerStateDir(h, name)
```
with:
```go
stateDir, err := resolveAbsoluteRunnerDir(h, name)
if err != nil {
    return fmt.Errorf("resolving state dir for %s: %w", name, err)
}
```

And in `removeContainer`, replace:
```go
stateDir := containerStateDir(h, instanceName)
```
with:
```go
stateDir, err := resolveAbsoluteRunnerDir(h, instanceName)
if err != nil {
    // fall back to unresolved path; rm -rf in the shell will still expand $HOME
    stateDir = containerStateDir(h, instanceName)
}
```

The `mkdir -p` and `rm -rf` shell commands already expand `$HOME` themselves, so they only need the fix when the path is wrapped in single quotes for Docker (the `-v` bind-mount argument).

